cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of wireless networks using cognitive radio technology. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as cognitive radio involves the transmission and processing of information. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of cognitive radio in mobile networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as cognitive radio systems involve control and optimization of network performance. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as cognitive radio systems may involve security and privacy considerations.
